title: For Sale:  Winchester 1886 40-82 WCF ca.
postcontent: Winchester Model 1886 in 40-82 WCF caliber. Serial number 7**53 placing production to approximately 1892. 26" Octagon barrel with bore showing good rifling and some minor light pitting. Original walnut stock shows and some edge loss on forearm and by upper tang. Markings are still pretty clear on barrel and tang. Missing riser on rear leaf sight. Action works well with an occasional failure to cock the hammer, likely due to lack of oil/cleaning over the years or slightly worn part as there is no push off of the hammer when cocked.Antique no FFL unless local law requires. Finish has turned to mostly to brown patina. An honest working gun that was in one family for at least 50 years and spent most of its time in the Dakota's. The 1886 was Winchester heavy action larger caliber rifle and was used extensively out west like this 1886. A handsome 1886 with character that deserves to go back out on the ranch.The best way to reach us is through e-mail. Postal money order only.
